WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.846
The adverse effects of myocarditis are clinically

00:00:02.846 --> 00:00:04.473
diverse and potentially fatal.

00:00:04.473 --> 00:00:07.319
Acute heart failure occurs in up to

00:00:07.319 --> 00:00:10.165
30 percent of hospitalized cases, with a

00:00:10.165 --> 00:00:13.012
subset developing fulminant myocarditis — characterized by

00:00:13.012 --> 00:00:15.858
rapid hemodynamic collapse and cardiogenic shock —

00:00:15.858 --> 00:00:18.704
carrying a short-term mortality exceeding 70 percent

00:00:18.704 --> 00:00:20.331
without mechanical circulatory support.

00:00:20.331 --> 00:00:23.177
Arrhythmias represent the second major category: ventricular

00:00:23.177 --> 00:00:26.023
tachycardia and fibrillation are the primary mechanisms

00:00:26.023 --> 00:00:28.869
of sudden cardiac death; complete AV block

00:00:28.869 --> 00:00:31.716
may require temporary pacing; and atrial fibrillation

00:00:31.716 --> 00:00:34.155
is common in the inflammatory phase.

00:00:34.155 --> 00:00:37.002
Thromboembolic events occur secondary to left ventricular

00:00:37.002 --> 00:00:38.628
dysfunction and endocardial inflammation.

00:00:38.628 --> 00:00:41.474
Chronic dilated cardiomyopathy develops in 10 to

00:00:41.474 --> 00:00:44.321
20 percent of patients, with persistent LV

00:00:44.321 --> 00:00:47.167
dysfunction at 6 months being the strongest

00:00:47.167 --> 00:00:49.200
predictor of adverse long-term outcomes.
